Content: There's no verifiable evidence. It also makes no sense that K64 asks investors to sign an NDA to attend an investor meetup and then ask the attendees to "make sure" they publish their experience.

Content: the best thing overall is to leave them be. as i said a few days earlier, you can't really expect to save everyone from a bad investment. as long as they don't leverage Komodo to take in more investments there isn't much we can do. however, i stand by my opinion that asking an investor to sign an NDA to attend an event that is supposed to convince people that they are a legit project while explicitly asking them to publish their findings makes 0 sense.
